---------------------------------------- file generated with WEIS QBlade API ----------------------------------------

---------------------- QBladeOcean Sub-structure definition file -----------------
200.0                         WATERDEPTH                - design water depth [m]
True                          ISFLOATING                - if the structure is fixed the joint coordinates are assigned in a coordinate system with O(0,0,0) at the mudline, for floaters O(0,0,0) is at the MSL and marks the floaters's NP
1025.0                        WATERDENSITY              -design density, used in flooded member mass calculations
0                             WAVEKINEVAL_MOR           - 0 - local evaluation, 1 - eval at fixed ref pos, 2 - eval at lagged position
0                             WAVEKINEVAL_MOR           - 0 - local evaluation, 1 - eval at fixed ref pos, 2 - eval at lagged position
30.0                          WAVEKINTAU                - time constant for the lagged waveKin position evaluation
100                           ADVANCEDBUOYANCY          - using an advanced discretization technique (N must be a square int number) to calculate buoyancy of partially submerged members, especially usefull if "lying" cylinders are used to generate the draft
----------------------------------------Potential Flow Opptions----------------------------------------------------------
False                         STATICBUOYANCY            - static buoyancy, based on the MSL should be used when using morison member buoyancy combined with potential flow diffraction forces
                              POT_RAD_FILE              - the potential flow radiation file
                              POT_EXC_FILE              - the potential flow excitation file
False                         USE_RADIATION             - use radiation forces [bool]
0.05                          DELTA_FREQ_RAD            - frequency resolution for radiation forces (used during interpolation of IRF)[Hz]
60.0                          TRUNC_TIME_RAD            - truncation time for radiation forces [s]
False                         USE_RAD_ADDMASS           - use added mass matrix provided in radiation file
False                         USE_EXCITATION            - use excitation forces [bool]
0.05                          DELTA_FREQ_EXC            - frequency resolution for excitation forces [Hz]
1                             DELTA_DIR_EXC             - direction resolution for excitation forces [deg]
60.0                          TRUNC_TIME_EXC            - truncation time for excitation forces [s]
                              POT_DIFF_FILE             - the potential flow diffraction file
                              POT_SUM_FILE              - the potential flow sum file
0                             DIFF_EVAL_TYPE            - evaluation type for difference frequency forces: 0-none, 1-explicit, 2-newman, 3-meandrift
False                         USE_SUM_FREQS             - use sum frequencies [bool]

